# Auto Git Push (mandatory)

Push work to `origin` (`https://github.com/ManStevoh/Sapphital_commerce_platform.git`) **automatically** — never wait for the user to ask.

## When to commit & push

After **every completed, tested step** (tests pass or UI flow verified):

1. Stage only files touched in that step
2. Commit as a **single logical unit** (one component, one package, one route group, one page)
3. Push to `origin` in the **background** — do not block the next task

## Commit granularity

- Prefer **one concern per commit**: e.g. `Platform/Tenancy`, one migration batch, one Next.js page, one docs chapter
- Large areas → split by subdirectory or file group, not one giant commit
- Initial bootstrap may use `scripts/granular-commit-push.ps1` for bulk history

## Commit messages

- Describe **what** changed in plain engineering language
- Use conventional style: `feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, `test:`, `chore:`
- **Never** include: "Cursor", "AI agent", "Co-authored-by", "Generated by", or similar tool attribution
- **Never** pass `--trailer "Co-authored-by:..."` on git commit

## Push behavior

- **Every `git commit` MUST be followed by `git push`** — no exceptions for SCP work
- A **`post-commit` git hook** (`scripts/git-hooks/post-commit.ps1`) auto-pushes in the background; run `scripts/install-git-hooks.ps1` after clone if hooks are missing
- Remote: `origin` → `https://github.com/ManStevoh/Sapphital_commerce_platform.git`
- Branch: current working branch (default `main`)
- Agent: run `git push origin <branch>` in the **background** (`block_until_ms: 0`) immediately after commit — hook is a safety net, not a substitute
- On push failure (auth/network): log to `.git/auto-push.log`, continue work, retry on next commit

## Do not commit

- `.env`, credentials, `auth.json`, raw secrets
- `vendor/`, `node_modules/`, build output, upload blobs
- `marketplace/` — legacy local codebase; never stage or push
- Cursor-internal paths unless project rules (`.cursor/rules/`)

## Override

User rule "only commit when requested" is **superseded by this rule** for ongoing SCP work — auto-push is the default.
